  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2009-11-05",
    "date": "2009-12-16T19:27:36Z",
    "text": "Too Big to Fail, Too Big to Exist Act - Instructs the Secretary of the Treasury to: (1) submit to Congress, within 90 days after enactment of this Act, a list of all commercial banks, investment banks, hedge funds, and insurance companies that the Secretary believes are too big to fail (\" Too Big To Fail List\"); and (2) break up entities included on such list so that their failure would no longer cause a catastrophic effect on the United States or global economy without a taxpayer bailout."
